3.5 stars, I rounded up.
Always looking out for the little guy.
I was going to try Carlito's one more time before I wrote a review.
My first visit was less than stellar.
But TBH, with so many go-to places in my neighborhood, not to mention over 3 pages of bookmarks, the chances of me returning to Carlito's in the near future is small.
My 3.5 stars is partially my fault.
I wasn't hungry at all but the bf loves Mexican so I looked up my Yelp bookmarks and saw Carlito's.
Big mistake.
Firstly Carlito's isn't Mexican, like Taco y Taco, imo it's more Americanized Mexican.
The restaurant boasts that it's New Mexican (as in, from New Mexico).
I've never been to New Mexico, but the cuisine seems to revolve around the Hatch green and red chile.
Their burritos are overstuffed, huge monstrosities, wrapped into a flour tortilla, then smothered with a chile sauce, and a slopping of cheese.
Forgive the faux pas, but it reminds me of the Green Burrito, maybe the Carlito's burritos are bigger.
They are absolutely delicious if you're drunk, sixteen, or just got out of prison.
I got their chicken salad, a huge monstrosity of shredded lettuce, beans, tomatoes cheese and chile.
It was ok, nothing special.
The thing that sets Carlito's apart is their over abundant use of the green chile.
I do love Hatch chile but I'm no connoisseur.
Maybe I have to taste more bad green chiles to truly appreciate the Hatch.
All I know is Carlito's does not skimp on their chiles.
It is in everything and it is in abundance.
So, if Hatch chiles are your thing, you'll love this place.
I also got their sopapilla (yuck) and their calabacitas (cut up squash).
Dunno, maybe New Mexican cuisine isn't for me, I wasn't impressed.
But one day when I'm famished I want to try their deep fried stuffed sopapilla.
I wasn't too thrilled with the set-up of the place.
Their soda station is right next to the line for the cashier.
It's a small place that gets packed.
So it was uncomfortable trying to stand in line while people were cutting in to get their drinks.
I did like the artwork hanging on their walls and they were for sale.
In the future, I will try this place again, but I will come hungry.

